tars. We find that $\\lesssim 1\\%$ of BH-NS\nmergers will have any mass ejection and about the same percentage will produce\nkilonova bright enough to have a chance of being detected with a large\n(Subaru-class) $8$m telescope. Interestingly, all these mergers will have both\na BH and an NS in the FMG.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Sep 2020 18:00:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Dec 2022 12:43:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-02"}
