 min sunspot\noscillation can be spatially resolved in the Doppler shifts. It may come from\nthe upper photosphere or the temperature minimum region and then propagate to\nthe chromosphere, which might be regarded as a propagating slow magnetoacoustic\nwave.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Sep 2020 09:21:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-28"}
